# Git workflow & parallelization

- For isolated feature work or risky changes: prefer using-git-worktrees / git-worktree to avoid contaminating main work.
- If work can be split (UI vs API vs docs vs tests): use dispatching-parallel-agents / subagent-driven-development.
- If you need help shaping clean history (atomic commits, tidy branches/PRs): use git-master.
